 Artichoke Filling and Tomato Sauce","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"39 g","fat":"39 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"40 g","calories":"2997 kJ \/ 715 kcal"},"usefulItems":"disposable piping bag or freezer bag, pastry brush","hintsAndTricks":["<i>Cooking cannelloni in your Varoma means the steam tenderises the pasta beautifully. Use this recipe as a starting point to create your own version – see our variations to help get started.<\/i>","Frozen artichoke hearts can be used instead of fresh or tinned.","<strong>Mushroom cannelloni:<\/strong> replace artichokes with <nobr>400 g sliced<\/nobr> fresh mushrooms. In <nobr>step 3<\/nobr> add mushrooms and white wine and, without measuring cup, cook <nobr><strong>15 min\/100°C\/speed 1.<\/strong><\/nobr> Drain mushroom mixture through simmering basket, return drained mixture to mixing bowl and continue recipe from <nobr>step 4.<\/nobr><br>- For meat-lovers, add <nobr>100 g pancetta<\/nobr> or bacon cubes in <nobr>step 4.<\/nobr>"],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","1h 35m","4 portions"]}